There are times when I’m looking in the mirror and I feel ‘fat’ There are times when I’m looking in the mirror and I feel ‘skinny’ I’m starting to believe it’s all in my head. These words should be for everyone. These words should be positive. I’m sick of being ashamed.

Hurtful words will exist as long as hurtful people do. I think reappropriating ‘bad’ words so that they mean something different or positive takes the power out of the verbal abusers hands. Telling someone they can’t say something only makes them want to say it more.

After these midterms I hope you have a greater believe in your voice. I hope you can find the strength to speak your truth to power. Imagine the change our voices can make together, from the sheer impact of our song. I hope you know your voice matters. Because it does.

But I had to get over thinking my voice was annoying. I had to get over the fact I thought I bored people or that the tone of my voice was too grating before I could be the girl who can speak self-love to 15,000 people in an arena. I had to believe that my voice mattered.

Public speaking wasn’t at what I thought I’d be doing. But I realize, connecting with you every night I’m on stage and here on social media has shown me my truest purpose. My voice isn’t annoying! Its valued! You care about what I have to say!

When I started doing interviews as an artist, Lizzo, I would be so surprised when the interviewer would actually listen to me. I’d wonder “why tf would they want to hear me speak for so long”... I would even ask them if it was ‘ok’ when my answers became long winded.
I used to hate the sound of my voice. I thought it annoyed people and my family. I tried not to talk too much so I wouldn’t bother any one with it.

So here’s my question: what is white culture? what is the cornucopia of white pride? I’m genuinely curious. Because if we all dig deep, & if culture wasn’t forcibly taken from black Americans then we all have an origin story on this planet & differences worth celebrating

Ie: Chinese culture is different than Japanese culture but according to white supremacy they’re considered “yellow”. Nigerian culture is different than Afro-Cuban culture but to yt supremacy they’re considered “black”. Stuffing culture into pantone MAKES NO SENSE.
White supremacy is funny because they’re the ones who made race a color. No one else in the world before imperialism found pride in calling themselves a color category. They found pride in Culture.

White men in power INTENTIONALLY enforced origin erasure so America would “belong” to them. Wild how Canada, the islands, north and South America are considered the Americas but when you see an “average American family” portrayed in the media they are white.

My favorite thing about him is that his Twitter bio says “American citizen of Scottish ancestry” He’s probably 3rd or 4th or even 5th+ generation but to acknowledge that his ancestors are not indigenous to the Americas is NEXT LEVEL.

Here’s to backfat, bootys, and beauty!
I know this feeling won’t last forever. There will be days when I can’t see the beauty. But this is the first day I’ve ever felt this way about my body and I’m going to enjoy it.
And tonight, in the middle of nowhere, I looked back at it and saw beauty. I wasn’t even expecting it. Just beautiful brown rolls stacked on a fat juicy ass. Yes!

It got annoying but I wouldn’t stop complimenting myself. I complimented others too! Friends... strangers.. Learning to say thank you when you’re complimented and not frantically trying to deflect is huge.

So I fucked with me. Like really fucked with me. Self praise, daily affirmations, exercising for MENTAL and physical health. Eating foods that made my mind and body happy. Flirting! Moving and exploring my body.

Then I realized: I’ll ALWAYS be insecure about my back fat because insecurity is internal. It’s a feeling. You can’t just wish it away with a wand. I realized I would have to win the war against this insecurity before my body could change.
But I listened to and sang “My Skin” too many times to go back on my promise to never let anyone take my beautiful skin away from me. Even if it could ‘cure’ my deepest insecurities.
Yes, Miss Love-Yourself-Body-Positivity Lizzo hated her back fat. And secretly, (wanted to just cut it off).
Here’s a confession: I have excess skin and back fat that I’ve always been insecure about.

I’ve ballooned in weight a lot, due to being an overweight kid then being broke and homeless, then eating my feelings, then becoming addicted to exercise, then finally dealing with an unhealthy “eat while you can” artist diet.
Mind you, I look back at it a lot. But normally clothed or with bra and panties on. This was the first time I’ve accepted my back and butt and thighs in their entirety.
Tonight was the first time I looked back at my ass, naked, in the mirror and loved what I saw in the reflection.
